</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,943,1185]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
Karyotype: 2n = 50 and FN = 68. Autosomal complement: two large subtelocentric pairs, eight metacentric and submetacentric pairs medium to small decreasing in size, and 14 acrocentric pairs (one large and the remaining medium to small decreasing in size). Sex chromosomes: X, an acrocentric (the largest chromosome of the complement); Y, a small acrocentric (
<bibRefCitation author="Patton, J. L. &amp; Silva, M. N. F." box="[487,720,1086,1113]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="319 - 337" refId="ref71013" refString="Patton, J. L. &amp; Silva, M. N. F. (1995) A review of the spiny mouse genus Scolomys (Rodentia: Muridae: Sigmodontinae) with the description of a new species from the western Amazon of Brazil. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 108 (2), 319 - 337." type="journal article" year="1995">Patton &amp; Silva 1995</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 331, 
<figureCitation box="[829,918,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1103,1127]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,189,1072]" captionTargetId="figure-17@32.[151,1436,181,1079]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Neacomys. (♦) N. dubosti; (☆) N. macedoruizi; (r) N. minutus; (○) N. musseri; (■) N. paracou; (l) N. rosalindae; (ê) N. spinosus; (◊) Neacomys sp.; (□) Neacomys sp. 1; (▲) Neacomys sp. 2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423633/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,943,1185]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
